Jennifer, David, Robert, William, Mary, James,   these six statues are arranged in a circle on the altar, each facing toward the center of the altar. The positions of the six statues correspond precisely to the six vertices of a regular hexagon. The distance between any two adjacent statues is equal, approximately one meter. It is known that:
(1)Robert is immediately to the right of David;
(2)James is at the first position when counted clockwise from Mary;
(3)Mary is at the first position to the left of David;
(4)Robert is the first one on the left side of William.
